      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "ce2eddcf1ca0c8c9",
      "text": "The ultimate goal for developing SOTCAC is to provide INTEL analysts with a larger context of ‘plausibly possible’ TNet ↔ CTNet coevolutions – as they could be – so that TNets can be better understood as they are and as they are likely to adapt. And since the way in which the CTNet collects, assimilates, fuses and derives inferences about what the terrorist ‘looks like’ is prescribed (via local, context-dependent properties and behaviours) – not scripted – SOTCAC may also help analysts discover novel data-fusion and ‘ground truth’ inference strategies."
